From c2e6936a62f6233324e496a28f318186fdc060b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan on Selwyn <dan@awto.au>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 11:59:32 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] lib: translate rational, bcd, hweight to Rust (linux-rs batch
 3, readiness-ranked)

First batch chosen by the vocabulary-transfer readiness metric
(scripts/readiness.py in the linux-rs repo): hweight/bcd were 100%
in-vocabulary after 6 TUs, rational 96.8% (one new construct: min()).

- rational: continued-fraction approximation; output params kept as
  pointer writes; wrapping arithmetic per C; MODULE_* macros dropped
  (no-ops for builtin, CONFIG_MODULES=n)
- bcd: trivial pair, C integer promotion made explicit
- hweight: faithful bit-parallel popcount incl. both
  ARCH_HAS_FAST_MULTIPLIER arms and the 32-bit arm via cfg; count_ones()
  left to the benchmark-gated optimisation lane

Validated: ok 11 rational (8/8 vectors) + all prior suites still green
on qemu -M virt boot; 9 Rust TUs in the kernel.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
